 Egra study sites-III, the highest annual zooplankton density was 1486.50 ind./L in ponds, with the lowest being 1259.00 ind./L in canals. At Haldia study sites-II, the highest density was 668.00 ind./L in ponds, and the lowest was 547.75 ind./L in canals. At Contai study sites-IV, the maximum density was 928.00 ind./L, with the minimum being 726.75 ind./L in ponds and canals, respectively. In Tamluk study sites-I, the highest density recorded was 1171.50 ind./L in ponds, with the lowest at 1057.75 ind./L in canals. Heavy metals (HMs) Table 1 47  Table 1 Descriptive statistics of the seven heavy metals of different study sites. Study area Statistical parameter Hg (µg/L) Pb (µg/L) Fe (µg/L) Cu (µg/L) Zn (mg/L) Cd (µg/L) Ni (µg/L) Tamluk Mean 0.85 3.56 0.18 4.16 8.74 2.57 8.54 Standard error 0.19 0.63 0.02 0.73 1.02 0.34 0.93 Standard deviation 0.66 2.18 0.08 2.52 3.54 1.19 3.22 Sample variance 0.43 4.74 0.01 6.36 12.54 1.42 10.38 Kurtosis − 1.08 − 0.26 − 1.08 − 1.08 − 1.35 − 0.33 − 1.33 Skewness 0.40 0.58 0.43 0.31 − 0.17 0.74 − 0.13 Range 1.90 6.83 0.23 7.37 10.31 3.41 9.33 Haldia Mean 2.06 5.83 0.58 7.07 9.48 5.77 8.46 Standard error 0.37 1.01 0.08 1.00 1.21 0.70 1.06 Standard deviation 1.28 3.49 0.28 3.46 4.20 2.42 3.68 Sample variance 1.65 12.20 0.08 11.94 17.61 5.84 13.57 Kurtosis − 1.31 − 1.41 − 1.30 − 1.48 − 0.86 − 1.15 − 1.00 Skewness − 0.19 0.16 − 0.21 − 0.30 0.01 − 0.72 − 0.28 Range 3.83 10.13 0.80 10.09 13.80 6.73 11.74 Contai Mean 1.77 4.86 0.39 6.30 7.93 4.05 8.05 Standard error 0.33 0.70 0.07 1.00 0.90 0.63 0.72 Standard deviation 1.13 2.41 0.25 3.48 3.13 2.18 2.50 Sample variance 1.28 5.82 0.06 12.10 9.82 4.75 6.26 Kurtosis − 1.51 − 0.63 − 0.97 − 0.55 − 0.70 0.35 − 0.10 Skewness − 0.31 0.01 0.68 0.31 0.61 1.16 − 0.37 Range 3.05 8.10 0.75 11.11 9.68 7.18 9.02 Egra Mean 0.84 3.34 0.14 2.55 10.23 1.88 6.22 Standard error 0.27 0.71 0.02 0.40 1.68 0.24 0.77 Standard deviation 0.92 2.47 0.08 1.39 5.82 0.85 2.68 Sample variance 0.85 6.12 0.01 1.93 33.82 0.72 